since it's very difficult to prove an advantage in the Sveshnikov, so many top
players are opting for this move.} e6 {This will be the recommended move
against the Rossolimo in this course, mainly because it's simpler to
understand and play in comparison to 3...g6.} 4. c3 (4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6.
Nc3 {This is a Four Knights system where the bishop is misplaced on b5.} Qc7 $1
