the pawn on e5.}) 18. Nxe5 Rfb8 19. b3 a4 $11) 11... Nb6 (11... a5 $5 {[%cal
Gc8a6,Ga5a4] Is another playable option for Black.} 12. exd6 exd6 $11) ({
A simple continuation suggested by the engines is:} 11... Ba6 12. exd6 exd6 13.
c3 Qd7 $11) 12. exd6 (12. Bf4 Nxc4 13. Bxc4 d5 14. Bd3 Be6 $11 {[%cal
Gc6c5,Gd8b6] Black will have nice central control with the pawns on d5 and c5
soon.}) 12... exd6 13. c3 Be6 (13... Nxc4 {This continuation is also fine for
Black.} 14. Bxc4 d5 15. Bd3 a5 $11) 14. Nxb6 axb6 (14... Qxb6 $11 {Recapturing
on b6 with the queen and putting some pressure on the b2-pawn is also possible.
}) 15. Bd2 d5 16. a4 c5 $11 {1/2 (22) Senzacqua,F (2025) -Lundberg,K (2015)
