also fine to recapture with the d-pawn.} 6... dxc6 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 {[%csl Rc3]
The knight is already on c3 and White doesn't have the plan that was mentioned
in the previous lesson which was f2-f3, Be3, and Nd2-Nc4.} 8. Bc4 Bb4 9. f3 Ke7
$11 {[%cal Gc8e6]})) (6. Nf3 Bb4 {It's logical to pin the knight, perhaps
threatening to capture it at some point.} (6... Bc5 {Is also good.}) 7. Bc4 (7.
Bd3 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 d6 9. O-O O-O $15 {[%csl Rc3,Re4] White's pawn structure is
damaged.}) 7... O-O 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 d6 {This move seems to be more
