leads to equality.} 10. Ba3 d6 11. Re1 Ng5 $11) 10. Qd3 (10. Ba3 Na5 $1 {
White has some issues now with the pawn on e4 and bishop on c4.}) 10... Re8 11.
Rd1 Be6 $132 {[%csl Rc3,Re4]}) (6. Nb3 Bb4 7. Bd2 (7. Bd3 d5 8. O-O d4 9. Ne2
O-O $15 {The structure with the d4 and e5-pawns is good for Black.}) (7. Bc4
O-O 8. Qd3 d5 9. Bxd5 Nxd5 10. exd5 Ne7 11. O-O Bf5 12. Qe2 Bxc3 13. bxc3 Qxd5
14. Ba3 Rfe8 $15) 7... Bxc3 8. Bxc3 O-O 9. Qf3 (9. Bd3 d5 {When 10.exd5 Nxd5
is good for Black.}) 9... d6 {The threat of Bg4 prevents 0-0-0, so White
