[%cal Gd8g5]}) 21... Qe8 (21... Rc4 $5) 22. b3 Bd8 23. h3 Rc7 24. c4 Re7 25. c5
Nd7 26. c6 Rxe4 27. cxd7 Qe7 28. Rxe4 (28. Qg4 Rxa4 29. bxa4 Rf7 30. Rxf4 Qxd7
$11) 28... Qxe4 29. h4 Qf5 30. hxg5 Qxd7 31. Rxf4 Rxf4 32. Bxf4 Bxa5 $11 {
1/2 (33) Chocenka,D (2461) -Windhausen,G (2535) ICCF email 2018}) 19... Bg5 $1
(19... g5 20. c4 Bf5 21. Kh1 $14) 20. Ra3 {There are a few good queen moves
for Black here.} (20. Nxc8 Rxc8 21. Bc3 Qe8 $11) 20... Qe7 (20... Qf6 $5 21.
Rc3 f3 $1 22. Bxf3 (22. Bxg5 Qxg5 23. Bxf3 Bh3 24. Qe2 Rf4 $44) 22... Nxf3+ 23.
Rcxf3 Qd4+ 24. Kh1 Bg4 25. Rxf8+ Rxf8 26. Rxf8+ Kxf8 27. Qf1+ Qf6 28. Qxf6+
Bxf6 29. Nc4 Be7 30. Kg1 (30. Bb4 Bf5 31. c3 Be4 32. Bxd6 Bxd6 33. Nxd6 Bxd5
34. Nf5 Kf7 35. Kg1 Kf6 36. Ne3 Ke5 37. Kf2 Bc6 $11 {[%cal Ge5e4]}) 30... Bf5
31. Ne3 Be4 32. Kf2 Ke8 33. c4 Bd3 34. b3 Bg5 $11 {1/2 (35) Ulasevich,S (2480)
-Zhdanenia,K (2310) ICCF email 2020}) (20... Qe8 $5) 21. c4 (21. Rc3 Bd7 22.
Rc7 Qd8 23. Nxd7 Qxc7 (23... Nxd7 24. Rc4 f3 $5 (24... Ne5 25. Rd4) 25. Rxf3
Rxf3 26. Bxf3 (26. gxf3 Bxd2 27. Qxd2 b6 $44) 26... Ne5 27. Re4 Bxd2 28. Qxd2
b6 $44 {[%csl Ge5]}) 24. Nxb8 Qc5+ 25. Kh1 Rxb8 26. Bc3 (26. h3 {1/2 (26)
Elyoseph,H (2432) -Pereira,E (2437) ICCF email 2022} Rf8 $11) 26... Re8 27. Qd4
Qxd4 28. Bxd4 Bf6 $11 29. Rxf4 $2 Ng6 $19) (21. h3 Bd7 22. c4 Rbe8 23. Nxd7
Qxd7 $11 {[%csl Ge5,Gf4,Gg5]}) 21... f3 $1 {A crucial dynamic pawn sacrifice.}
22. Bxf3 (22. Bxg5 Qxg5 23. Bxf3 Bh3 24. Qe2 Rbe8 25. Re3 h6 $44 {We have
enough counterplay.}) 22... Bxd2 23. Qxd2 Bg4 $1 {Very critical.} 24. c5 (24.
Bxg4 Rxf1+ 25. Kxf1 Nxg4 26. Kg1 Rf8 27. Rf3 Rxf3 28. gxf3 Ne5 {[%csl Ge5]} 29.
Kg2 Qf6 30. Qe3 Qg6+ $11 {White's king is too weak for him to make use of the
pawn advantage.}) 24... Bxf3 25. gxf3 Rf5 26. f4 Rbf8 27. Rc3 g5 (27... Ng6 $5
28. Qe3 Qf7 $11 {Another equalizing option.}) 28. c6 Rxf4 29. Rxf4 gxf4 30. h3
(30. c7 Qxc7 {[%cal Ge5f3] The tactical justification of Black's play.}) 30...
bxc6 31. dxc6 f3 32. Qf2 {Black draws without difficulty.} (32. c7 $5 f2+ 33.
Kf1 Nd3 $1 {Here we need to play this move!} (33... Qg7 $2 34. Qxf2 $1 Rxf2+
35. Kxf2 $18 {wins for White!}) 34. Rxd3 Qg7 35. Rg3 Qxg3 36. Qd5+ Kg7 37. Qd4+
Kh6 38. Qd2+ Kg6 39. Qc2+ $11) 32... Qc7 33. Nd7 Nxd7 34. cxd7 Qxd7 35. Rxf3
Rxf3 36. Qxf3 Qb5 $11 {1/2 (38) Lanz Calavia,J (2407) -Magat,G (2327) ICCF
