20. gxf4 b4 21. fxe5 Bxe5 22. Ne3 bxc3 23. bxc3 Kh8 $44 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Ge7g6]
}) (18. a4 bxa4 19. Ne3 Rfb8 20. Nc4 Rb3 21. Ra2 e4 $11) 18... f4 $1 {One of
the major ideas in these positions. Black splits his pawns but activates his
bishop.} 19. gxf4 exf4 (19... Kh8 $5) 20. a3 Ng6 21. Qh5 Rfe8 $11 {1/2 (28)
Shablinsky, M (2443) -Fischer, W (2478) ICCF email 2014}) (15. Nc2 {Transposes
to the previous lessons.}) 15... e4 16. Bc2 {This is one of the main lines,
but it is absolutely harmless. Black gets a lot of activity and White's play
