are a pawn down, but our kingside are already pretty dangerous for White.})
17... Bxb2 18. Rab1 Bc3 19. Qh6 Rb8 {As mentioned above, all that White can
hope here is restoring material parity and equality:} 20. Rb3 a5 21. a3 Ng6 22.
axb4 axb4 23. Rfb1 Qf6 24. Nxb4 Ne7 25. Qxf6 Bxf6 26. Nc6 Rxb3 27. Rxb3 O-O $11
{1/2 (41) Zhekov,Z (2337) -Gaehler,S ICCF email 2018}) (14. Qh5 e4 15. Be2 Bg7
16. c3 O-O 17. Nc2 {Transposes to the previous lessons.}) 14... Bg7 15. Nc3 e4
16. Be2 (16. Bc4 O-O 17. Qh5 (17. Qd2 Ng6 18. Kh1 Be5 $44 {[%csl Ge5] 1/2 (43)
